I'm creating a workflow with a custom code which I can update an association label, but completely stuck for far too long now on an error I can't figure out.

Here is my call:
```  var config = {
    method: 'PUT',
    url: '<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v4/objects/contact/'+ContactRecordID+'/associations/deal/'+dealid+'>',
    headers: { 
      'content-type': 'application/json', 
      'Authorization': auth,
	body: {
    "associationCategory": "USER_DEFINED",
    "associationTypeId": 151
    }
    }
  };```
And here is the error i am retrieving:
```    data: {
      status: 'error',
      message: 'Invalid JSON input: a request body was expected, but none found',
      correlationId: '672c837e-2931-4ad9-96e8-8f9f5c6cd111',
      category: 'VALIDATION_ERROR'
    }```
Is anyone able to help figure out what's wrong with my api call? I did try sending the data in 'data', and as a saved json.stringify-ed variable. All failing :(

For reference i found out my issue. I'm posting the fix here incase it gets anyone else (it was obvious..) as i hadn;t sent it via data with the [ ] brackets.
Working call below:
```    method: 'PUT',
    url: '<https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v4/objects/contact/'+ContactRecordID+'/associations/deal/'+dealid+'>',
    headers: { 
      'content-type': 'application/json', 
      'Authorization': auth,
  },
  data: [{ 
    "associationCategory": "USER_DEFINED",
    "associationTypeId": 152
  }]
};```
